Comparison of salamander abundance by channel classification in old growth and clear cut sections of Mack Creek

Table 1. 2017 salamander counts by channel classification in old growth and clear cut sections of Mack Creek
Section Cascade Pool Side Channel
Clear Cut 43 (69%) 5 (8%) 14 (23%)
Old Growth 35 (65%) 8 (15%) 11 (20%) 
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  chi_counts
## X-squared = 1.3274, df = 2, p-value = 0.5149

According to our Chi-squared test for independence, there is not a significant effect of forest condition on where in the channel salamanders are found.

Salamander weights in clear cut versus old growth sections in 2017

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  weight by Section
## t = 1.6669, df = 692.79, p-value = 0.09599
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.2121307  2.5972032
## sample estimates:
##  mean in group Clear Cut mean in group Old Growth 
##                 7.775870                 6.583333

In 2017, the mean salamander weight at the clear cut sites was 9.84, and the mean salamander weight at the old growth sites was 8.28. The mean lobster size between clear cut sites and old growth sites did not differ significantly (t(692.79) = 1.67, p = (0.096) with a small effect size of 0.13.
